## Session 2 — abbreviation SELECTION rule (§5c), captured-output mining + live probes

### Corpus reads (captured OUTPUT: oracle/dot_corpus/, oracle/captured_responses/)
- Enumerated manifest URL families: main/proof (json, 14705) pairs 1:1 with
  interactive-graph-def (dot, 14705); the main/proof json html carries the full
  UNABBREVIATED sequent (Constraint system: formulas/goals/solved+unsolved
  constraints), while the dot carries abbreviated terms + legend. Mined these
  pairs at scale for a labeled abbreviate/not dataset.
- Parsed all 97 538 legend expansions across 11 564 graphs: min fully-expanded
  rendered length = 10 (0 below); 0 legend entry is a top-level tuple.
- Built AST parser for tamarin printed terms (fact-arg extraction, name
  expansion, structural subterm occurrence). Ran per-graph labeled evaluation
  over up to 5 725 graphs / 156 602 candidates. Findings: len>=10 & occ>=2 &
  not-tuple is necessary with 0 counterexamples among drawn->=2 terms; all
  "missed" abbreviations have graph-occ 1 (recovered from the sequent);
  sufficiency exceptions are 93% AC/DH-operator graphs (occurrence over the
  normalised term), rest are expand-before-count artifacts.
- Confirmed abbreviation universe > drawn nodes: SI3='sign(~y, k)' is a legend
  entry drawn NOWHERE in its graph (only in the sequent).

### Live server probes (hs_server binary, --port= form; crafted theories)
Served four one-rule theories whose single graph node carries controlled terms;
solved the exists-trace lemma via GET /main/method/<lemma>/1 (returns a redirect
to a new theory index), then GET interactive-graph-def/proof/<lemma>/_ .
- LenTest: Keep(~x,'12345678','12345678','1234567','1234567') ->
  '12345678'(10 chars,x2) abbreviated as `2`; '1234567'(9,x2) inline.
  => length threshold is exactly 10.
- OccTest: 'ABCDEFGH'(10,x1) & 'onceonly12'(12,x1) inline; 'twicelong1'(12,x2)
  => TW1. LongOnce: a 42-char constant (x1) inline; 'shared1234'(x2) => SH1.
  => occ>=2 is a hard gate independent of length.
- TupTest: <'aa','bb','cc'>(18,x2) inline; h('longarg123')(x2) => H1, with
  LO1='longarg123', H1='h(LO1)'. => tuples never abbreviated; bottom-up nesting;
  prefix rule (lo->LO, h->H) re-confirmed live.
- Servers stopped after probing. Note: pure-numeric constant got empty prefix =>
  bare-number name ('12345678' -> "2"); empty-prefix start index not pinned.
